Template: nightwatcher/db_password
Type: password
Description: NightWatcher database password:
 The daemon connects to its MariaDB/MySQL database as the 'nightwatcher' user.
 This password is written to /etc/nightwatcher/nightwatcher.env (mode 0600, read
 by the service) and is never stored in the package or in git.
 .
 Leave blank to set the database up yourself later, then re-run:
 dpkg-reconfigure nightwatcher

Template: nightwatcher/db_host
Type: string
Default: 127.0.0.1
Description: Database host:
 Host of the MariaDB/MySQL server, optionally with a ":port" suffix. Use
 127.0.0.1 for a server on this machine, or a hostname/IP for a remote one.

Template: nightwatcher/db_create
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Create the 'nightwatcher' database and user now?
 When the database is local and this machine's administrator can reach
 MariaDB/MySQL over its root socket, the database and application user are
 created automatically with the password above (the daemon builds the tables and
 seeds an admin login on first start). Choose no to run the shipped
 sql/setup.sql yourself.

Template: nightwatcher/api_bind
Type: string
Default: 127.0.0.1
Description: Web UI / API bind address:
 Address the built-in HTTP server listens on. 127.0.0.1 serves only this
 machine; 0.0.0.0 serves the whole network. Bound off localhost, every request
 (reads included) requires a login or API token.

Template: nightwatcher/api_port
Type: string
Default: 8080
Description: Web UI / API port:

Template: nightwatcher/api_tls
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Serve the web UI / API over HTTPS?
 When enabled and no certificate exists yet, a self-signed certificate is
 generated automatically (browsers show a one-time warning you can accept).
 Recommended when binding off localhost.

Template: nightwatcher/start_now
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Start the NightWatcher service now?
 Safe once the database is reachable. If you let this installer create the
 database above, it is fine to start now; otherwise start it later with:
 systemctl start nightwatcherd
